prompts.frontCover: A charming and slightly wobbly, tiered birthday cake, illustrated in a loose watercolor style. The cake is comically leaning to one side, as if about to topple over. A single, determined candle sits jauntily on top, its flame flickering bravely. Whimsical, colorful frosting drips are captured with soft, bleeding paint effects. Splatters of pastel watercolor paint in shades of pink, teal, and sunny yellow surround the cake on a textured paper background, adding to the playful, messy-but-artistic feel. In the center, written in a beautiful, flowing, and easily readable handwritten cursive script, is the text: "It's all downhill from here... but at least there's cake!" Flat 2D artwork with visible brush strokes and organic paint bleeds.
